===Records set===
The following records were set in Super Bowl XXI, according to the official NFL.com boxscore, the 2016 NFL Record &amp; Fact Book and the Pro-Football-Reference.com game summary. &lt;br&gt;Some records have to meet NFL minimum number of attempts to be recognized. The minimums are shown (in parentheses).


Turnovers are defined as the number of times losing the ball on interceptions and fumbles.


This is also the first, and only time in history, an NFL game ended with a final score of 39–20.

